Key Match Events: Namibia secured a super over win over Oman in a thrilling finish
Ruben Trumpelmann started off brilliantly, dismissing Kashyap Prajapati on the first ball of the match
Bilal Khan got an early breakthrough for Oman, dismissing van Lingen for a duck
Pre-Game Insights: Namibia Captain Gerhard Erasmus said they would bowl first and look to execute their skills in the middle
Oman Captain Aqib Ilyas said they would bat first and look to execute their plans
Post-Match Reflections: Gerhard Erasmus said it was difficult to get momentum through the innings, but they proved that there are runs to be had if you assess the pitch well and take responsibility
Aqib Ilyas said credit goes to Namibia, and they should have gone for more runs when they were set
David Wiese said he had a feel for the wicket and knew what he had to execute in the Super Over
Miscellaneous Highlights: The pitch at Kensington Oval was difficult, with a lot in it for the bowlers
The new ball did tend to swerve around a bit under lights
Namibia and Oman have a head-to-head record of 3 matches, with Namibia winning 2 and Oman winning 1
